observations.recommendation:
Recommendation:
Enjoin the Office of the Municipal Treasurer and the Office of the Municipal Accountant to prioritize the reconciliation of the RPCI and accounting records;

Enjoin the Office of the Municipal Treasurer to exclude in the Property Cards all Inventory asset accounts and instead record them in  separate stock cards;

Require the concerned officers to maintain stock cards and supplies ledger cards for each item of Inventory to ensure proper accounting and promote better control in the receipt and issuance of supplies; and,

Require the concerned office to submit proof of issuance/ distribution or liquidation of the inventory assets of CY 2022 to properly reflect the correct balance of the Inventory asset accounts.

Recommendation:
Enjoin the Inventory Committee, headed by the Municipal Treasurer, and the Municipal Accountant to identify the cause of the variance between the physically counted PPEs and the Accounting records and reconcile them; 

Assign one personnel from the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to reconcile the Property Cards with the RPCPPE; 

For the local road networks, enjoin the Municipal Engineer to provide the value and cost in the Road Network Inventory; and,

Maintain subsidiary ledger cards for roads and road components of every road network and prepare lapsing schedule showing the computation of the depreciation of each component of the Road Network System account.

