observations.recommendation:
Recommendation:
Require the Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the cashbook balance with the accounting records every end of the month and take up immediately necessary corrections in books requiring adjustments to reconcile both the cashbook and the ledger; 

Direct the Municipal Accountant to match liquidations with the specific cash advance granted when recording the settlement of cash advances in the ledger.

Recommendation:
For proper financial statements presentation, we recommend dropping from the Books of Accounts the amount of ₱45,000.00 representing the cost of the two (2) breeding stocks after making the necessary and required relief from accountability by the accountable officer having the custody of the property;

Considering, however, that the loss/death of the two hybrid goats were not properly documented, there being no showing that the death of these goats was investigated upon or referred to the COA Auditor, we require to recover the amount of loss from the accountable officer having the custody of the property.

Recommendation:
Ensure strict compliance with the provisions of Republic Act 9003 in proper segregation, collection, transport, storage, treatment, and disposal of solid waste. Ensure the implementation of segregation at the source of solid waste, enforcement of the “no segregation, no collection” policy, creation of a Materials Recovery Facility (MRF) in every Barangay, and the development of disposal facility in the Municipality;

Expedite the closure of the open dumpsite; instead, commence the operations of the MRF and/or consider an alternative dump site;

Hire additional personnel that will man the equipment and operations of the MRF, if needed; 

Assign a safe parking area with cover to protect the trucks from man-made and natural calamities; and,

Enjoin the SWM Team to create and present a detailed plan to implement the project, programs, or activities for which the equipment for alternative technologies is intended.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:
enjoin the Property Custodian to conduct a complete physical count of all PPE and prepare a report using the prescribed format;
create a committee composed of one personnel each from Treasurer’s Office and Accounting Office who shall reconcile their respective records of PPE on a full time basis and at the same time maintain an updated and complete PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards;
For the Road Networks, direct the Municipal Accountant to record all road networks and its components, based on the Registry of Public Infrastructures, or in its absence, based on the complete Local Road Inventory Report provided with complete description and cost segregation of the road components and provide proper disclosure of the road networks in the Notes to Financial Statements;
direct the GSO to maintain an updated Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card of all roads within its area of jurisdiction; and
if warranted, enjoin the Municipal Accountant to adjust in the books the discrepancies identified during the reconciliation.

We recommended and Management agreed to require the accountable/ responsible officers to:

Conduct physical count of the local road networks and submit the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System;

Prepare a complete Report on Local Road Networks, maintain local road inventory, road map and property cards for all roads and its component;
Maintain subsidiary ledger cards for roads and road components of every road network and prepare lapsing schedule showing the computation of the depreciation of each component of the Road Network System account;

Disclose the total Road Network System account in the Notes to Financial Statements and make adjusting entry regarding depreciation and derecognition of the replaced asset following the provision of COA Circular 2015-008; and

Provide a complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended and Management agreed to: 

Require the concerned officers and employees to settle and/or liquidate their cash advances and strictly adhere to the rules and regulations on the grant, utilization and liquidation of cash advances;

Instruct the Office of the Municipal Accountant to monitor the grant of cash advances, enforce strictly the prompt liquidation thereof; and no additional cash advance be granted if previous cash advance has not been liquidated;

Send final demand letters to officers and employees previously employed by the Municipality, otherwise, officials responsible for clearing said individuals from money accountability be held liable for the unsettled cash advances; and

Request for authority to write-off the unliquidated cash advances especially those pertaining to deceased accountable officers.

We recommended and Management agreed to direct the Municipal Accountant to:

Prepare the journal entry voucher (JEV) for the unadjusted reconciling items of reciprocal accounts and update recording of transactions at all times; and

Trace the difference of ₱2,917,546.83 existing between the Due from Other Funds and Due to Other Funds accounts to show a reconciled amount in the financial statements;

We recommended and Management agreed to:

ensure that payments are made directly to suppliers/creditors in the form of checks and only petty operating expenses should be reimbursed through the Petty Cash Fund; 

direct the payment as obligations fall due without resorting to advances from personal funds of officials and employees.

We recommended and the Municipal Treasurer agreed to: 


Closely monitor collections made by collectors and require them to remit collections daily and intact;

Deposit intact all collections to authorized depository banks; and

